<P>9. In its federal/BC income tax return for the federal/BC taxation year ended June 30, 2003, Veracity allocated 89.8% of its taxable income to Quebec, and 10.2% of its taxable income to BC. This was the result of the application of the income allocation formula under which $99 of its total gross revenue of $163,754, and $2,000 of its total $9,795 of salaries and wages, were attributable to a permanent establishment in BC (the rest was from Gaz Metro, attributable to Quebec).</P>
